Description: Glazed steatite rectangular plaque inscribed on one side with the prenomen and nomen of Ramses 2 and epithets, longitudinally pierced, the other side inscribed with a cartouche enclosing the Egyptian name Maathorneferura of the Hittite princess married to Ramses II by the year 34 treaty.
Curator's comments: Published Kitchen, Ram. Insc. Vol 2 p857
Bibliographic references: Monaco 2008 / Queens of Egypt: from Hetepheres to Cleopatra
Exhibition history: Exhibited: 1998/9 Oct-Jun, South Carolina, The Charleston Museum, Queens Commoners of the New Kingdom 2008 Jul-Sept, Grimaldi Forum, Monaco, Reines de Egyptes
